cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes a framework for adversarial training that focuses on samples rather than single sample points. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the application of the framework to domain adaptation, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes two distributional adversaries that operate and predict on samples, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the stability and mode collapse of models, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SD) sub-category.
